			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>The Semantics of Plurals</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/FriedrichSteimann.html">Friedrich Steimann</a>, <a href="../profile/MariusFreitag.html">Marius Freitag</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567516">10.1145/3567512.3567516</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagM">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It develops the meaning of plural (bunch) expressions and their evaluation semantics.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> The paper effectively proposes a language design extension for plural/relational expressions.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It relies on formal semantic reasoning (bunch theory and relational interpretation).
</li></ul></li></ul>
